Notes: The 'row_id' serves as a unique identifier for each prescription, directly mapping to the 'hasIdentifier' property with an appropriate datatype of string.
The 'patient_id' links to the patient entity associated with the prescription, making this path semantically appropriate.
The ATC code represents a coded classification of the drug, which aligns with the 'hasCode' property of the Code entity.
Diagnosis codes are represented as coded entities; mapping to 'hasCode' provides semantic clarity.
The creation date is a datetime value, directly mapped to the 'hasDateTime' property with datatype dateTime.
The 'times_a_day' indicates frequency of administration, which aligns with the 'hasFrequency' property of Quantity.
Dosage specifies the amount administered, best represented by the 'hasDrugQuantity' property.
